args:
Though the party manages to fend off Beren,
Nedrick's body is unable to withstand the primal
powersâ€”so the prince accepts them in his
stead, then returns them to the Greatwyrms
using the power of their pacts.
That does it for the terminals!\nNow all that's left...
I understand how noble your desires were,\nHolywyrm, but you shouldered too much\non your own.
I wish you'd believed in us a bit more.
You're not the only one trying to protect\nthis world, you know? But no need to\nworryâ€”we understand you now.
So let us respond to your feelings in kind...
You promised me long ago that you\nwould protect this world, Elysium.

And yeah, maybe you went about it in a
way we couldn't accept, but you were
willing to sacrifice your entire self just to
keep that promise.
So now it's my turn to carry on your wish\nand protect this world as your pactbearer!
I have caused you all so much pain...
You have freed me from the malice\nof the Progenitor.
But I do not have long to maintain myself,\nand will soon become mana once more.
I regret that I can no longer watch over\nthis magnificent world...
Our way of thinking may be different from\nyours, but that's the only thing we've ever\nwanted to do in the end.
And I swear we will never betray that wish.
I give you my thanks, child of man.\nAnd as for my fellow dragons,\nI leave this world in your hands.
I loved this world...with all my heart...
I'll see you again someday, Elysium.\nI promise.
And after all the trouble I went through\nto get my hands on the Holywyrm...
You're the last obstacle for us, Beren!
But there is one thing making me feel\na bit better: the cretin who destroyed\nmy world appears to be at his limit.
The primal powers are too much\nfor a human body to handle.
Poor thing. You finally managed to defeat\nthe Holywyrm, but now you're about to die.
I think I'll take my leave now. That man did\ntell me not to use too much of my power.
I will see you again, my dear siblingsâ€”\nand I pray you better understand how the\nworld truly works when I do.
I wonder if we'll ever understand\neach other...
It'll be tough, but I still don't want to\ngive up on the idea entirely.
But right now, we need to help Nedrick.\nIf the primal powers are causing this,\ncan we save him by taking them away?
Yes. If we Greatwyrms reclaim our primal\npowers, they will no longer eat away at\nyour companion.
Well, they belonged to us in the first place,\nso it makes sense for us to take 'em back.
N-no... I cannot give them to you...
We've not the time for this! You will perish\nif you attempt to hold claim on them!
Now hurry up and fork 'em over!
It is not a question of desire or want...\nThere is simply...no way to return them...
I understood...once I took the powers...\nThey have already become one...

So the primal powers can no longer be
divided five ways as they once were?
Perhaps this is a result of their having
resided in Elysium for so long.
Even if Nedrick were to set the primal\npowers free, there isn't anyone who can\naccept them.
And if we set them free without anyone\nelse to quell them...they will rage out\nof control...

Those powers were strong enough to
withstand Bahamut's will for destruction.
If they run unchecked, the entire world
will be in danger!
Which means...I cannot let go of them!
But again, and I hate to keep harping\non this, YOU DIE IF YOU DON'T, DUDE.

The only one who could take in the Five
Greatwyrms' combined power is someone
as powerful as Bahamut. And while we
have one more pactbearer among us...
If I could take his place, I wouldâ€”but I\nwas unable to withstand Bahamut even\nwithout his primal powers.
Hmph... It simply means I must....keep\n...control...
No. Nedrick. You must give them to me.
I am pactbound with all the Greatwyrms,\nso I should be able to handle all of\ntheir powers.
No! I won't permit you to suffer in the\nsame way this man is now!
Don't worry about me, Mym.\nI have you by my side, after all.
You, Midgardsormr, Mercury, Jupiter,\nand Zodiark. All of you give me strength.
...Ugh. Of COURSE that's where he went.
Bringing up the power of bonds again, eh?\nDo you really think something so uncertain\ncan control power like this?

It's not uncertain at all. 
The primal powers belong to the Five
Greatwyrms, so it only makes sense that
we should make use of their strength.
Besides, I don't have any intention of\ncontrolling themâ€”they're far too powerful\nfor one person to hold.
Well, I suppose I was the one who said\nyou were able to do what I could not, so...
Very well. Let me see what you can do.
The primal powers... Nnngh...\nThey're tearing me apart...!
D-don't worry about me... I'm going to...\nreturn this power to you...!
All of the Greatwyrms...stand ready...\nI'm returning your primal powers now!
You really ARE fascinating, aren't you?
I'm starting to remember what our\nprimal powers felt like...
I've felt your powers since the moment\nwe were pactbound, so I know everything\nthere is to know about them.
And with the power of our pact and bond,\nI should be able to return them to you!
So this is my primal power...?\nThis is the real me...?
Aaaah ha ha ha! This is wonderful!
We've finally reclaimed our primal powers!
To think you are capable of separating the\nprimal powers united under Elysium...
It is nothing short of a miracle.
Oh, I KNEW you could do it, darling!\nYou just make me fall for you more\nand more every day!
I give you my thanks, pactbearers.
Without you, the Greatwyrms of the present\nwould not have been able to regain their\npower.
We should be thanking you for what\nyou taught us about the past.
Thanks are not needed; I left a fragment\nof my will here for that exact purpose.
And now that I told you all you need to\nknow, my purpose has been fulfilled.
My time to become mana grows nigh.
Wind of the present, I will watch over you\nas a part of the wind. Never forget that the\nworld is on our side...
I have accepted the will of the wind,\nmy ancestor. May you rest soundly.
